OL,3,CParliament to vote on granting
OL,4,CGovernment control of British Steel
OL,6,FThe plans would see taxpayer money
OL,7,Fused to provide materials to the
OL,8,Fsteelworks and open the door to a
OL,9,Ftransfer of ownership after Sir Keir
OL,10,FStarmer warned the future of the firm
OL,11,F"hangs in the balance".
OL,13,FMinisters hope to secure a private
OL,14,Fpartner to open up co-investment
OL,15,Foptions for a transition but urgent
OL,16,Ftemporary action was seen as necessary
OL,17,Fto keep the plant running until longer-
OL,18,Fterm plans are agreed.
