OL,3,CParliament to vote on granting
OL,4,CGovernment control of British Steel
OL,6,FUnions welcomed the move but Tory
OL,7,Fleader Kemi Badenoch accused Labour of
OL,8,Fhaving "bungled the negotiations" and
OL,9,Fsaid "their incompetence has led to a
OL,10,Flast-minute recall of Parliament."
OL,12,FLiberal Democrat Sir Ed Davey called
OL,13,Fthe debate an opportunity to advance
OL,14,F"a serious plan for the sustainable
OL,15,Ffuture of domestic steel production"
OL,16,Fwhile Reform UK leader Nigel Farage
OL,17,Freiterated his backing for
OL,18,Fnationalisation.
